Police in Edo have arrested a 63-year-old grandfather, Sunday Igbinokhuaihe, for defiling a two-year-old girl. The rape took place at Urhonigbe in Orhionmwon Local Government Area of Edo state, with the suspect being a neighbour to the parents of the victim. It was gathered yesterday in Benin that Igbinokhuaihe lured the little girl into his room with a loaf of bread, while using his finger to break her hymen, at a time the victim’s mother was preparing dinner in the kitchen for members of her family. The mother was shocked when her daughter screamed when she was bathing her in the evening of the same day, with the victim opening up on what earlier transpired, making her mother to raise the alarm. A report was lodged at the Urhonigbe police station, leading to the suspect’s arrest and later transfer to Abudu divisional police headquarters. Igbinokhuaihe was later transferred to the State Criminal Investigation Department (SCID) of Police spokesman Chidi Nwabuzor confirmed the arrest of the suspect. A human rights group, in Port Harcourt, Rivers State, Centre for Basic Rights Protection and Accountability Campaign (CBRPAC) has called on the Ignatius Ajuru University of Education (IAUE), Rumulomeni, in Obio/Akpor Local Government area of the state to release the employee of the institution Mgbechi Wekwe accused of defiling a 16-year-old stepdaughter to the police for questioning. Wekwe, a security official of the university, allegedly abducted and defiled the girl to punish his estranged wife, Kindness Edwin. The school is allegedly frustrating efforts of the victim and her mum to get justice. The university has denied the cover-up allegation. The group called on the visitor to the school, Governor Nyesom Wike, the State Ministries of Education,Women and Social welfare, the general public to prevail on the university to produce the suspect for proper investigations.